    <subsection xml:id="subsec-ch04-pdf-glossary">
      <title>Glossary</title>
      <p><term xml:id="term-probability-distribution-function">probability distribution function (PDF)</term>: a mathematical description of a discrete random variable (<em>RV</em>), given either in the form of an equation (formula) or in the form of a table listing all the possible outcomes of an experiment and the probability associated with each outcome</p>
